# Specs

Implementation plans for {{REPO_NAME}}.

## Convention

- Filenames are `NNNN-<short-feature-name>.md`, zero-padded sequence number first (`0001-bootstrap.md`, `0002-add-export.md`, ...).
- One plan per independent piece of work. Multi-subsystem efforts get split into separate plans.
- Plans use the format defined by the **`jojo-skills:writing-plans`** skill — checkbox-tracked, bite-sized steps, exact paths, real code (no placeholders).

## Status

- `specs/0001-bootstrap.md` — the seed plan written when the repo was created. Likely a stub; flesh out or supersede as the project takes shape.

## Adding a new plan

Ask Claude (or whichever agent you're using) to write a plan for the next piece of work. The `writing-plans` skill should trigger automatically on phrases like "let's implement X" or "I want to add Y" — if not, invoke it explicitly. The next sequence number is whatever comes after the highest file in this directory.
